Strategic Implementation Roadmap
We break the launch into 4 independently testable, high-fidelity milestones targeting a premium product aesthetic (matching modern tools like Airbnb and Stripe).

Milestone 1: Visual Identity & Secure Onboarding (Days 1–3)
Deliverables:
Onboarding and landing layout utilizing a clean, high-contrast, professional palette (Inter font, slate grays, clean typography, soft card shadows).
Dynamic Registration/Login screen with multi-step onboarding forms:
Role selection (patient / physio).
Physio-specific verification fields (License, Aadhar, Degree Certificate upload targets).
Strict route routing rules using client-side auth context hooks.
Verification Strategy: Automated routing tests with mock unverified and verified user accounts to ensure dashboard isolation.

Milestone 2: Service Area & Scheduling Engine (Days 4–6)
Deliverables:
Availability Management Console for physiotherapists: Interactive grid to toggle days and define specific daily operational hours.
Service Area Configurator utilizing Google Places Autocomplete API with coordinate extraction (lat, lng) and a dynamic sliding radius selector (in km).
Live profile rendering component illustrating therapist biography, expertise badges, operating area, and interactive calendar.
Verification Strategy: Validation test suites assessing correct parsing of weekly recurring slots and coordinate generation.
Refactorings:
1. Recommended Improvement: In Milestone 2/3, refactor the wizard to use React Hook Form paired with localized controllers. Uncontrolled input refs will prevent keyboard render choking.
2. Recommended Improvement: Decouple credentials immediately. Keep aadharCardNumber and attached certificationFileName strictly within an isolated collection path (e.g., /physio_credentials/{userId}). Create security rules permitting access exclusively to the owning clinician and administrative system roles.
3. Recommended Improvement: Ensure that subsequent database calls are secured with strict Firestore Security Rules that match the user's role and verification status on the server.
4. Recommended Improvement: Standardize on ISO 8601 offset strings (e.g., appending local offset context or storing server timestamps).
5. Recommended Improvement: Move all static mocks and lists into a dedicated helper file (e.g., src/lib/mocks/userMocks.ts) to keep the context code clean.

Milestone 3: Search Discovery & Haversine Geolocation (Days 7–9)
Deliverables:
Discovery Marketplace Page for Patients: High-end search dashboard matching the aesthetic of premium services.
Google Places search input enabling patients to set search centers.
Haversine distance calculating algorithm running client-side to filter out therapists whose declared service area does not encompass the patient's coordinates.
Card-based listing layout displaying therapist name, specialization, distance (calculated to 1 decimal place), and quick-view capabilities.
Verification Strategy: Visual testing using varying patient coordinates to confirm perfect filter accuracy on mock therapist operational bounds.

Milestone 4: Transactional Booking & Review Engine (Days 10–12)
Deliverables:
Booking Request Drawer: Fully integrated on-page selector enabling date and slot reservation.
Transactional booking creation pipeline executing check-and-write locking inside the Firestore SDK to guarantee zero double-booking concurrency bugs.
Real-time Request Dashboards:
Physiotherapist Portal: Incoming request queue with quick "Accept" / "Decline" buttons.
Patient Portal: Live status feed showing pending, accepted, and completed sessions.
Review Submission Dialog: Automatically locks to "completed" bookings; enables patient star rating and feedback text.
Verification Strategy: Simultaneous client-browser execution testing to confirm transaction resolution on double-booking attempts.
